@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Privacy</title>
</head>

<body>
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <section>
    <h2>Welcome to your Music Library Website!</h2>
    <p>Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, share, and protect your information when you visit our website, use our services, or interact with us in any way.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect various types of information to provide you with a seamless experience on our platform:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> When you create an account, we may collect information such as your name, email address, and other contact details.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Information:</strong> We collect data related to your interactions with our website, including browsing activity, tracks you listen to, playlists you create, and other preferences.</li>
        <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> We may collect information about the device you use to access our services, such as the type of device, browser information, and IP address.</li>
    </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use your information for various purposes, including:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Providing Services:</strong> To help you find and save albums, singles, and tracks that you love.</li>
        <li><strong>Improving User Experience:</strong> To personalize your experience on our website, recommend content, and develop new features.</li>
        <li><strong>Communication:</strong> To send you updates, newsletters, or promotional materials (you can opt-out anytime).</li>
        <li><strong>Security and Compliance:</strong> To protect our users and comply with applicable laws and regulations.</li>
    </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
    <h2>Sharing Your Information</h2>
    <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share your information with trusted third parties to help provide our services, including:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> We may share information with vendors who assist us in running our platform (e.g., hosting, analytics, or customer support).</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to valid legal requests.</li>
    </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
    <h2>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
    <p>We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your browsing experience. You can control the use of cookies through your browser settings, but please note that some features of our site may not function properly if cookies are disabled.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have questions or concerns about our privacy practices, please contact us at:</p>
    <p>Email: <a href="mailto:support@musiclibrary.com">support@musiclibrary.com</a></p>
    <p>Thank you for using your Music Library Website. We value your trust and are committed to protecting your privacy.</p>
    </section>
</body>
</html>